article.headline: W. Kentucky 86, Fla. International 74
article.story: MIAMI (AP) -- Tyrone Brazelton scored 21 points to lead Western Kentucky to a 86-74 win over Florida International Thursday. Western Kentucky (13-5, 5-1 Sun Belt Conference) ended the first half with a 38-35 lead, and Florida International (6-10, 1-5 SBC) couldn't catch up. Besides being the game's top scorer, Brazelton also hit four out of four 3-point shots. Western Kentucky's Ty Rogers scored 19 points, and Orlando Mendez-Valdez scored 16. Alex Galindo scored 20 points for Florida International, while Chris Fuller added 18, and Johwen Villegas added 14.
